items.title: Limosa haemastica
items.content_text: Distinguished from Bar-tailed Godwits by the partial white eyebrow; paler upper parts, and in flight a clear black tail and white rump with dark underwing.

items.title: Ixobrychus dubius
items.content_text: A rare pair of breeding Little Bitterns!

items.title: Calidris minuta
items.content_text: This bird is in breeding colour... much brighter orange-rufous than the colours of the Red-necked Stint - I have left the Red-necked Stints in for comparisons. In the primary picture you can also see the white 'line' across the mantle (upper back) of which the two lines from the rear appear as a loose V and is one of the diagnostic features of a Little Stint.

items.title: Haematopus finschi
items.content_text: Flagged 1N; the SIPO is smaller than an Australia POC, has visibly shorter legs and longer, thinner bill. In flight, the underwing is almost entirely white.

items.title: Lophoictinia isura
items.content_text: Getting fantastic views of this gorgeous raptor has been one of the highlights of the year so far. By the time I swapped the binoculars for the camera it had moved away a reasonable distance.
